@node "Test" "Server checks"


@{b}TESTS & CHECKS@{ub}
--------------


After the server installation and configuration to check the fully
functionality of the system you can do the following tests:


                             @{" HTTP-Test " link "HTEST"}
                             @{" FTP-Test  " link "FTEST"}
                             @{" IRC-Test  " link "ITEST"}

                         @{" Problem resolution " link "PROB"}

@endnode

@node "HTEST" "HTML pages test"


@{b}HTTP-Test@{ub}
---------

- Run Amitcp typing "Startnet"

- Open any browser. Write the previously defined URL address
  (Ex. name.bbs.org)

- If all is working right you'll get a simple HTML page. Otherwise
  check all settings.

@endnode

@node "FTEST" "FTP test"


@{b}FTP-Test@{ub}
--------

- Run Amitcp typing "Startnet"

- Open any FTP client (AmFTP, MFTP,...).

- Connect to the server typing the previously defined address

- If the FTP server is working right you should be brought in the
  directory @{" FTP " link "Ftp" ('FTP DRAWER'}. Otherwise check
  if the FTP drawer exists.

@endnode

@node "ITEST" "IRC test"


@{b}IRC-Test@{ub}
--------

- Run Amitcp typing "Startnet"

- Open any IRC client

- Connect to the server typing the previously defined address

- Open a second client.

- Connect the second one to the server, too.

- Now the first client should be connected to the second one.
  Otherwise check all settings.

@endnode

@node "PROB" "Problem resolution"

If you cannot succefully made anyone of the tests please, do not contact
us before you checked:

   @{b}1) the @{" installed archives " link "Requ"} must be the right ones.

   2) The AmiTCP: assign is available.

   3) The paths added by Amitcp must not have dupes (Check it using
      the 'path show' command)

   4) the address assigned to the server is the right one@{ub}

@endnode

